          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X']]></fr:tex> be preschemes that are of finite type and flat over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  X\to  X']]></fr:tex> be a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex>-morphism.
    For <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> to be an open immersion (resp. an isomorphism), it is necessary and sufficient that the induced morphism on the fibres
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       g\otimes _Y k(y)\colon        X\otimes _Y k(y) \to  X'\otimes _Y k(y)     ]]></fr:tex>
    be an open immersion (resp. an isomorphism) for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  Y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  
    
